<li>Ligaments<ul><li><em>Falciform Ligament<\/em><ul><li>Separates Medial &amp; Lateral Left Lobe<\/li><li>Attaches to Anterior Abdominal Wall &amp; Extends to Umbilicus<\/li><li>Contains Ligamentum Teres<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li><em>Ligamentum Teres (Round Ligament)<\/em><ul><li>Contained in Free Edge of Falciform Ligament<\/li><li>Carries Remnant Umbilical Vein<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li><em>Ligamentum Venosum<\/em><ul><li>Remnant Ductus Venosus<\/li><li>From Ligamentum Teres to IVC<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li><em>Portal Triad<\/em><ul><li>Contained within Hepatoduodenal Ligament<\/li><li>Enters Porta Hepatis<\/li><li>Contents: <a class=\"button\" style=\"background-color: #193556; padding: 2px 7px; border-radius: 2px;\" href=\"#MN\">Mn <\/a><ul><li>Lateral: Bile Ducts<\/li><li>Medial: Proper Hepatic Artery<\/li><li>Posterior: <strong>Portal<\/strong> <strong>Vein<\/strong><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>*A Pulse Felt <strong>Posterior-Lateral<\/strong> May Be from a Replaced Right Hepatic Artery from the SMA<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li><em>Epiploic Foramen (Foramen of Winslow)<\/em><ul><li>Entrance of Lesser Sac<\/li><li>Borders:<ul><li>Anterior: Hepatoduodenal Ligament<\/li><li>Posterior: IVC<\/li><li>Superior: Caudate Lobe of Liver<\/li><li>Inferior: Duodenum<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-21f69b3 elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"21f69b3\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor